WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.480
With your RStudio Cloud account, you'll have access to your own personal workspace,

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:12.160
as well as the ability to create additional workspaces.

00:00:12.160 --> 00:00:16.160
As an educator, you might find it helpful to create a single workspace for each of your

00:00:16.160 --> 00:00:18.400
classes or workshops.

00:00:18.400 --> 00:00:23.000
This creates a shared space for all of the learners within a class, allowing you to create

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:26.879
and share assignments with your learners, as well as provide learners with a place to

00:00:26.879 --> 00:00:28.719
complete their coursework.

00:00:28.719 --> 00:00:34.759
What's more, you can view the work of your learners by going into their RStudio projects.

00:00:34.759 --> 00:00:39.919
Once we log in to RStudio Cloud, navigate to the menu on the left by clicking here.

00:00:39.919 --> 00:00:44.160
We can also choose to keep this menu open by clicking on this pin.

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:48.560
Here we see my personal workspace, as well as a series of workspaces that I've created

00:00:48.560 --> 00:00:49.799
or joined.

00:00:49.799 --> 00:00:53.959
We can create a new workspace by clicking on this New Space button and naming our new

00:00:53.959 --> 00:00:55.279
workspace.

00:00:55.279 --> 00:01:02.320
For the purposes of this example, I'll call our workspace Fall 2021 Data Visualization.

00:01:02.320 --> 00:01:06.959
Once we're in the workspace for a course, we can create projects, add co-teachers and

00:01:06.959 --> 00:01:11.839
teaching assistants, as well as add learners and change access permissions.

00:01:11.839 --> 00:01:15.760
These are all topics covered in additional videos, and I encourage you to check out our

00:01:15.760 --> 00:01:17.919
RStudio Cloud playlist to learn more.

00:01:25.279 --> 00:01:26.279
Thank you for watching.

00:01:26.279 --> 00:01:27.279
If you have any questions, or would like to ask a question, please post them in the chat

00:01:27.279 --> 00:01:28.279
box.

00:01:28.279 --> 00:01:28.279


